ğŸ§  Brain Tumor Detector & Classifier

A Deep Learningâ€“powered web application for classifying brain tumors from MRI scans.

âš ï¸ Medical Disclaimer

This project is intended strictly for educational and research purposes.
It is NOT a medical diagnostic tool and must not be used for clinical or professional healthcare decisions.
Always consult a qualified medical practitioner for real medical concerns.

ğŸŒŸ Overview

The Brain Tumor Detector & Classifier is a web-based tool that uses a fine-tuned deep learning model (VGG16-based CNN) to classify MRI brain scans into the following categories:

Meningioma Tumor

Glioma Tumor

Pituitary Tumor

No Tumor Detected

The web interface is built using Flask, enabling users to upload MRI images and receive predictions with confidence scores.

âœ¨ Features
âœ” Image Classification

Upload an MRI image and get a tumor category prediction.

âœ” Multi-Class Prediction

Classifies images into 4 classes:

Meningioma

Glioma

Pituitary

Healthy (No Tumor)

âœ” Confidence Score

Displays the modelâ€™s confidence as a percentage.

âœ” Medical Summary

Provides short educational info and suggests which medical specialist to consult (e.g., neurologist, neurosurgeon).

âœ” Simple Web Interface

Clean UI built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

