ğŸ”§ Installation Guide
1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Thanatos624/BrainTumorDetection
cd BrainTumorDetection

2ï¸âƒ£ Create and activate a virtual environment
Windows
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

macOS / Linux
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

3ï¸âƒ£ Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4ï¸âƒ£ Download the dataset

Dataset: Brain Tumor MRI Dataset (Kaggle)
Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets

After downloading:

Unzip the dataset.

Copy the Training folder into the project:

project_root/training/dataset/


The folder structure should look like:

training/dataset/
 â”œâ”€â”€ glioma_tumor/
 â”œâ”€â”€ meningioma_tumor/
 â”œâ”€â”€ no_tumor/
 â””â”€â”€ pituitary_tumor/

ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Training the Model (Optional)

A pre-trained model is already included at:

model/brain_tumor_model.h5


If you want to retrain:

python training/Brain_Tumor_Training.py


This will:

Load & preprocess the dataset

Fine-tune VGG16

Save the trained model in model/

â–¶ï¸ Running the Web Application

From the project root:

python app.py


If Flask starts successfully, you'll see something like:

Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000/


Open your browser and navigate to:

ğŸ‘‰ http://127.0.0.1:5000/
